\v 25 \x + \xo 11:25: a \xt Acts 16:22; \xo b \xt Acts 14:19.\x*was beaten three times with rods, was stonedВҰ124707 once, shipwreckedВҰ124709 three times, and I was in the ocean for a dayВҰ124710 and a nightВҰ124710.
\v 26 \x + \xo 11:26: a \xt Acts 9:23; \xo b \xt Acts 14:5.\x*I've done \add many long\add* trips, crossed dangerous riversВҰ124718, risked being robbedВҰ124720, \add was persecuted\add* by my own people as well as by non-Jews, have been in danger in the cityВҰ124729, in the wildernessВҰ124732 and on the ocean, \add as well as being attacked\add* by falseВҰ124738 \add teachers\add*.
\v 27 I've worked often and worked hard, often needing to keep guard, \add suffered\add* famineВҰ124747 and thirstВҰ124749, fasted often, and been coldВҰ124754 and lacking clothing.
\v 28 \add Then\add* apart from all those externalВҰ124759 things, I've been opposed every dayВҰ124767вҖ”\add not to mention\add* my concern for all the assembliesВҰ124772.
